-- Ambuja, EIH, Jet Airways, Lupin, Strides Arcolab,: India Equity Preview
-- B y   M a d e l e n e   P e a r s o n
-- 2010-09-24T02:50:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/eih-jet-airways-india-lupin-strides-arcolab-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or  Sensex , fell
80.71, or 0.4 percent, to 19,861.01. The S&P CNX  Nifty  Index on
the National Stock Exchange declined 0.5 percent to 5,959.55.
The  BSE 200 Index  decreased 0.4 percent to 2,509.85. SGX CNX
Nifty Index futures for September delivery were little changed
at 5,966.5 at 10:48 a.m. in Singapore.  Ambuja Cements Ltd.  (ACEM IN): The unit of Holcim Ltd., the
world’s second-largest cement maker, was downgraded to
“reduce” from “hold” by Lakshminarayana Ganti, an analyst at
BNP Paribas Securities (Asia), with a 12-month price estimate of
109 rupees per share. Ambuja fell 1.2 percent to 145.8 rupees.  EIH Ltd.  (EIH IN): The operator of India’s luxury Oberoi
hotel chain said its board approved a rights issue to raise as
much as 13 billion rupees ($285 million), in a statement sent by
e-mail. Billionaire  Mukesh Ambani ’s Reliance Industries Ltd.
owns about 14.8 percent of EIH. EIH lost 0.5 percent to 139.6
rupees.  Jet Airways (India) Ltd.  (JETIN IN): The nation’s biggest
carrier will start a daily non-stop flight from New Delhi to the
Italian city of Milan from Dec. 5, the company said in an e-
mailed statement yesterday. The stock added 1.9 percent to 807.1
rupees.  Lanco Infratech Ltd.  (LANCI IN): The infrastructure company
has plans to set up large thermal power plants in Tamil Nadu and
Andhra Pradesh to achieve operating capacity of 4,000 megawatt
by the end of March 2011, the Financial Express reported,
without saying where it got the information. Lanco retreated 1.9
percent to 67 rupees.  Lupin Ltd.  (LPC IN): The generic-drug maker expects sales
to grow 22 percent in the year ending March 31,  Ramesh Swaminathan , the company’s finance chief, told reporters in
Mumbai yesterday. The stock added 3.7 percent to 399.25 rupees.  Strides Arcolab Ltd.  (STR IN): The drugmaker plans to raise
as much as $100 million in a share sale to large investors,
according to a sale document obtained by Bloomberg News. The
shares will be sold for at least 423.55 rupees each, the
documents show. The stock lost 0.1 percent to 434.55 rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
